  "title": "山核桃大街谋杀案",
  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\121-山核桃大街谋杀案-阿加莎克里斯蒂.txt",
  "chunk_index": 29,
  "summary": "During an outdoor lunch in Regent's Park, Archibald tells Sally Finch that he has been distracted by the recent events on Chestnut Street. He mentions an interest in boric acid, noting that Mr. Chandra Lal had previously used a white powder of the substance from a small white bottle to wash his eyes, but the bottle has since gone missing.\n\nIn a separate conversation, Gene asks Valerie for advice regarding a matter of conscience. Gene reveals that he accidentally searched through Nigel's briefcase several weeks prior and discovered a passport containing Nigel's photograph but a name such as Stanford or Stanley. Gene suspects Nigel is living under a double identity and wonders if Nigel murdered Celia because she discovered the fake passport. Valerie dismisses this theory, explaining that Pat told her Nigel had signed a contract to change his name for money. Offended by Valerie's skepticism, Gene leaves. Afterward, Valerie tells Sally that she finds Gene's behavior terrible and suspects he might be a murderer. Valerie also expresses her belief that Mrs. Nicolaitis was likely killed and suggests there is a \"nutcase\" among their group.\n\nLater, Pat approaches a frantic Nigel, who is searching for lost notes. Pat confesses that while mending his socks, she found a bottle of morphine in a drawer. Nigel claims he had previously told her he obtained the morphine from a hospital and intended to dispose of it after a certain bet, noting that he had not yet obtained a \"third thing.\"",
